---
// src/pages/gate.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBlock from "../components/NavBlock.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Gate | Quirgs"
  description="Human oversight infrastructure for AI agents. The HITL Gate sits between an AI agent and any action it cannot take autonomously."
  terminalPath="~/gate"
>
  <NavBlock currentPath="/gate/" />

  <div class="line">
    <span class="prompt">admin@quirgs</span><span class="path">~/gate</span
    ><span class="text-bright">$</span>&nbsp;cat gate.md
  </div>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <div class="detail-header">
    <h1 class="text-bright">Quirgs HITL Gate</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Human oversight infrastructure for AI agents.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="text-bright positioning-line">
    Static guardrails are provably insufficient.
  </p>
  <p>Skills teach governance. The gate enforces it.</p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">WHY STATIC GUARDRAILS FAIL</h2>
  <p>
    Natural language is infinitely ambiguous. Guardrail rule-sets are
    necessarily finite. An adversarial formulation capable of bypassing any
    static, finite guardrail set will always exist — Gödel's incompleteness
    theorems apply directly to alignment-by-rule-set. Absolute model alignment
    is formally undecidable.
  </p>
  <p>
    NIST AI RMF guidance has pivoted accordingly: point-in-time and
    pre-deployment vetting are no longer sufficient. Compliance now demands
    continuous runtime behavioral analytics and dynamic containment — including
    human escalation at the point of risk, not just before it.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">WHAT IT IS</h2>
  <p>A lightweight checkpoint API backed by Cloudflare D1.</p>
  <p>
    When an AI agent produces output that requires human sign-off, it POSTs to
    the gate. The event sits as pending until a reviewer approves or rejects it
    at <a href="/review/">quirgs.com/review</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Every decision is logged. Every approval is timestamped.<br />
    That is your audit trail.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">WHY IT EXISTS</h2>
  <p>
    EU AI Act, NIST AI RMF, and ISO 42001 all require demonstrable human
    oversight — not claimed.
  </p>
  <p>
    <code>PATCH /events/{"{id}"} {'{"status":"approved"}'}</code> is the proof.<br
    />
    <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
    A timestamp is not a policy.<br />
    A timestamp in a queryable log is an audit trail.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">HOW IT WORKS</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>AI agent POSTs a pending event to the gate</li>
    <li>Reviewer sees it at <a href="/review/">quirgs.com/review</a></li>
    <li>Reviewer approves or rejects</li>
    <li>Reviewer tells the agent the outcome and the agent proceeds</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="token-block">
    <div class="line"><span class="text-yellow">[RESUMPTION]</span></div>
    <div class="line">
      Step 4 is conversational, not automatic. The agent's turn ends after
      posting — it does not poll the gate for a decision. Once a reviewer
      approves or rejects, you (or your orchestration layer) tell the agent the
      outcome to resume it.
    </div>
    <div class="line text-bright">
      No built-in webhook-to-agent callback ships today. Full six-step pattern:
    </div>
    <div class="line">
      <a href="/hitl/#wire-it-to-an-agent">WIRE IT TO AN AGENT</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    No vendor lock-in. No dashboard fees.<br />
    Runs on Cloudflare. Bearer token auth. Open source.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">EARLY ACCESS</h2>
  <p>The gate is in early access.</p>

  <div class="line">Request credentials: <a href="/support">/support</a></div>
  <div class="line">Subject line: HITL Gate — early access request</div>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p class="text-bright">
    Or self-host and deploy your own instance from the <a
      href="https://github.com/unqdlphn/quirgs"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener">repo</a
    >.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <div>
    &rarr; <a href="/hitl/">/hitl/</a> docs and integration walkthrough
  </div>
  <div>&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    &rarr; <a href="/review/">/review/</a> human review queue (requires write token)
  </div>
  <div>&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    &rarr; <a href="/demo/">/demo/</a> see a live demo queue
  </div>
  <div>&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    &rarr; <a href="/resources/ai-risk-profile-case-study/"
      >Risk Profile case study</a
    >
  </div>
  <div>&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    &rarr; <a href="/resources/case-study-zero/">Case Study Zero</a> — 25 checks,
    live production, three real bugs found and fixed
  </div>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <div class="line">
    <span class="prompt">admin@quirgs</span><span class="path">~/gate</span
    ><span class="text-bright">$&nbsp;</span><span class="cursor"></span>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .positioning-line {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    font-weight: bold;
  }
</style>
